
{{alias}}( x, x0, Ɣ )
    Evaluates the logarithm of the cumulative distribution function (CDF) for a
    Cauchy distribution with scale parameter `Ɣ` and location parameter `x0` at
    a value `x`.

    If provided `NaN` as any argument, the function returns `NaN`.

    If provided `Ɣ <= 0`, the function returns `NaN`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    x: number
        Input value.

    x0: number
        Location parameter.

    Ɣ: number
        Scale parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    out: number
        Evaluated logCDF.

    Examples
    --------
    > var y = {{alias}}( 4.0, 0.0, 2.0 )
    ~-0.16
    > y = {{alias}}( 1.0, 0.0, 2.0 )
    ~-0.434
    > y = {{alias}}( 1.0, 3.0, 2.0 )
    -1.386
    > y = {{alias}}( NaN, 0.0, 2.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 1.0, 2.0, NaN )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 1.0, NaN, 3.0 )
    NaN


{{alias}}.factory( x0, Ɣ )
    Returns a function for evaluating the logarithm of the cumulative
    distribution function (CDF) of a Cauchy distribution with scale parameter
    `Ɣ` and location parameter `x0`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    x0: number
        Location parameter.

    Ɣ: number
        Scale parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    logcdf: Function
        Logarithm of cumulative distribution function (CDF).

    Examples
    --------
    > var mylogCDF = {{alias}}.factory( 1.5, 3.0 );
    > var y = mylogCDF( 1.0 )
    ~-0.805
